so that (denoting concentrations by square brackets) [A] [G] == k\C~\ for
some constant k. The reaction C->B-\-G will of course proceed at a rate proportional to [C],
i.e. to [A] [G]. If the amount of C is always small compared with the amount of G one can
say that the presence of the catalyst and its amount merely alter the mass action constantDownloaded from https://royalsocietypublishing.org/ on 17 June 2025
