  (v)
  Statistical theory describes in detail what irregularities arise from the molecular
  nature of matter. In a period in which, on the average, one should expect a reaction to
  occur between n pairs (or other combinations) of molecules, the actual number will, differ
  from the mean by an amount whose mean square is also , and is distributed according to
  the normal error law. Applying this to a reaction proceeding at a rate F (s.u.) and taking
  the volume of the cell as 10- 8cm3 (assuming some elongation tangentially to the ring) it
  will be found that the root mean square irregularity of the quantity reacting in a period
  r of time (s.u.) is 0*004 J{F t).
